cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.DS 

The paper deals with clustering of large-scale multi-view images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel approach that involves binary compression, which is a technique used in machine learning and data compression. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.MM (Mathematical Methods). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves reducing computational time and memory footprint, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
